-- Ex-Qwest Chief Nacchio Awaits Ruling Today on Bid to Cut Six-Year Sentence
-- Joel Rosenblatt
-- 2010-06-24T16:50:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/ex-qwest-chief-nacchio-awaits-ruling-today-on-bid-to-cut-six-year-sentence.html

          
          
             A federal judge weighing a bid by
Qwest Communications International Inc.’s former chief Joseph
Nacchio to cut his six-year sentence said 63 months to 78 months
in prison is possible.  
 U .S. District Judge Marcia Krieger said today’s hearing in
Denver will resume later, when she will hear further arguments.
Krieger said she plans to make a ruling on Nacchio’s bid before
the end of the day.  
